The paper proposes a deep learning approach for Human Attribute Recognition (HAR) with a focus on improving attribute localization. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the proposed approach involves a coarse-to-fine attention mechanism, which is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The experiments are conducted on image databases, indicating that the paper may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves feature learning and attention mechanisms, which are also relevant to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
